description: Gets the mobile device access override for the given WorkMail organization, user, and device.

parameters.name: OrganizationId
parameters.description: The WorkMail organization to which you want to apply the override.

parameters.name: UserId
parameters.description: Identifies the WorkMail user for the override. Accepts the following types of user identities: User ID: 12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012 or S-1-1-12-1234567890-123456789-123456789-1234 Email address: user@domain.tld User name: user.

parameters.name: DeviceId
parameters.description: The mobile device to which the override applies. DeviceId is case insensitive.

nested_items.name: UserId
nested_items.description: The WorkMail user to which the access override applies.

nested_items.name: DeviceId
nested_items.description: The device to which the access override applies.

nested_items.name: Effect
nested_items.description: The effect of the override, ALLOW or DENY.

nested_items.name: DateCreated
nested_items.description: The date the override was first created.

nested_items.name: DateModified
nested_items.description: The date the description was last modified.
